title: Thunderstorms
body:
Natasha x reader

AN: I really like this. it was my first attempt at angst even though that’s not the order I’m posting it in. But oh well! Enjoy!💖

You storm through the front door of your house. “I can’t believe you.” You scream out as you throw down your bag and coat. “I was trying to protect you” Natasha calmly stated as she walked down the stairs. “You told Fury to take me out of the majority of missions. I’m going on one mission a month, if that, AND I have Bucky and Steve breathing down my neck 24/7 when I’m on said missions” brushing your hand through your hair. “What am I meant to do with my powers, I’m a useless member of this team.”

You had the powers similar to Thor’s and with Thor back in Asgard you had become a valued member of the team.

“Y/N I had to. You are barely in control of your powers, your dangerous. We can’t risk it.” Nat said, brushing a strand of hair from your face. You jerk back. “If I’m that dangerous then maybe you shouldn’t touch me” You spat.

She sighs, “You are being ridiculous Y/N and you know it. Once you learn and regain control of your powers then you’ll be able to go on more missions. We can’t just think about you in this situation; you could potentially put the rest of the team in danger.”

Clenching your first, you felt the energy run through your veins; spinning around you punch the wall directing all your energy into your fists. As you do so, bolts of lighting surround your hand and the power cuts out. You are left in darkness as a thunder storm beats on New York heavily.

“Did they make you feel better?” Nat snapped, crossing her arms firmly. “Y/N I’m tired; I’m tired of having to tread on eggshells around you. I love you Y/N don’t get me wrong. I really do. But you need to regain control, you have to. Just look outside. Look at what you caused. You can’t just cause raging thunderstorms every time you are angry or upset. You can’t live like this and neither can I.” Natasha hissed that last sentence. You flinched at her words, knowing she was right. But hearing it from the woman you loved, felt worse then being shot at; and she’d been shot at a lot.

“Nat, don’t you think I know this. Don’t you think I know I’m loosing control. Don’t you think I know that I’m ruining your life. But we could’ve talked about this before you spoke to fury. Before you spoke to the rest of the team. If you would’ve spoken to me before you went to fury, I would’ve agreed with you. I would’ve come with you.” The words tumbling out of your mouth. “But you didn’t trust me and that’s what hurts the most. You didn’t trust me to be apart of a decision that is based around me. Obviously you didn’t think I’d agree with you. Obviously you thought I’d fight against you if you had told me beforehand. But you are wrong; because I wouldn’t have. I would’ve agreed with you wholeheartedly.” You turn and head towards the door.

“No. Y/N. Please. We’ve both made mistakes. C’mon Y/N/N.” Natasha whimpers behind you.


Risking once last glance back, you mutter under your breath “at least I find peace in the rain.”

summary: Concept: It’s the final battle of Avengers 4. The Avengers are down for the count and Thanos is laughing, gloating that he has...
body:
Concept:

It’s the final battle of Avengers 4. The Avengers are down for the count and Thanos is laughing, gloating that he has won again. Suddenly, a stray arrow hits the Infinity Gauntlet. 

Thanos looks at the arrow and says, “Did you really think your arrow was going to do anything?”

Then Hawkeye smirks and says, “…tick tick, boom”. The arrow blows up, destroying the Gauntlet and scattering the Infinity Gems all across the area. 

BONUS: Thor walks up to him and asks Clint where he got the special arrow from. Clint then shrugs and says, “Hard to believe but some drunk woman with a blue cape said that I needed to use this to help you”.

summary: If Thanos’ snap was real what if we went to the soul world. But all of our pets banded together to help the remaining Avengers...
body: If Thanos’ snap was real what if we went to the soul world. But all of our pets banded together to help the remaining Avengers defeat Thanos. Like our dogs with their amazing sense of smell would detect bombs and other weapons. Our horses for transportation. The cats for emotional therapy. Birds as spys. And Mice and other small animals could sneak into buildings and spaceships and carry information. Also, our snakes could choke the enemies or hold them down. And maybe Shuri or Tony make armor for our pets.
